{"id": 231250628, "title": "Vote for your favourite place to eat and drink by the sea in Northern Ireland", "text": "Northern Ireland may not have the weather to rival Spain but when the sun is out, we think it is one of the most beautiful places in the world. So when the good weather does finally make an appearance, it is not surprising that we flock to be by our stunning beaches and take in some incredible views. If you aren't the kind to get the wetsuit on and go for a paddle, you may prefer to take in some seaside views with a nice cocktail in hand or enjoying a tasty meal. Read more: Great places to eat and drink by the sea in Northern Ireland Read more: First ever 30+ only festival to be held in Belfast this summer Last week we shared a list of some of the most popular spots in Northern Ireland to eat and drink by the sea while it began to feel a little bit like summer. And while the temperatures have unfortunately taken a dip this weekend, we want to be optimistic and hope that the gorgeous weather is just on the horizon. So to be prepared for the sun to (hopefully) appear this summer, we want to see what bars and restaurants by the sea are Belfast Live's audience's top picks. We are asking our readers to vote in our poll below to find out where their favourite place to eat and drink by the sea in NI is. Vote below in our poll... The results will be posted on our website next week. For all the latest news, visit the Belfast Live homepage here and sign up to our What's On newsletter", "summary": "For when the sun (hopefully) appears", "url": "https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/whats-on/food-drink-news/vote-your-favourite-place-eat-29308594", "image": "https://i2-prod.belfastlive.co.uk/whats-on/be/article20265322.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/1_outside-christmas.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 13:28:15", "author": "Sophie McLaughlin", "authors": ["Sophie McLaughlin"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.308}